OL,3,CHow to protect yourself from phone
OL,4,Ctheft as incidents spike over summer
OL,6,FFormer police detective Rebecca Mason
OL,7,Ftold ITV News that when overseas on
OL,8,Fholiday, the risk increases massively.
OL,10,F"You're in an unfamiliar area, you're
OL,11,Fmore relaxed, you're often more
OL,12,Fdistracted as well, and thieves take
OL,13,Ffull advantage of this, especially in
OL,14,Fbusy, crowded, popular areas.
OL,16,F"We're seeing places like Brazil, for
OL,17,Fexample, a nationwide blacklist
OL,18,Fsystem, so if a phone is stolen, it is
OL,19,Fblocked from being used on any other
OL,20,Fnetwork.
